args: So the monster who forced you to kill\nis in this very church?
That's right. He's trying to train a new\ngeneration of assassins as we speak.
We'll open the way, Alex—you just give\nthat damn priest the lesson of his life.
Thank you all for your help.
No thanks needed; we want to see this\npriest go down as badly as you do.
Uh, guys? Don't wanna freak anyone out\nhere, but I thiiiink we're surrounded.
These are my assassins.\nAlex's successors, if you will.
They're not nearly the blade in the dark\nthat she was...but they're capable enough.
I see I made one mistake when I turned\nmy back on my former life...
I never should have left a devil\nlike you to roam free.
But I will right that error here and now!
Aaaah ha ha! Me? A devil?\nThen what does that make YOU?!
She only did as she did because\nyou forced her hand!
Now now, that is simply not true!\nAll I did was show Alex a path.\nShe walked it herself—and gladly.
We have not come here to bandy about\nsemantics with you!
Ah, but the girl had SUCH natural talent...
Old man? You got three seconds to shut\nyour yapper before we do it instead.
Come now! There's no need for threats.\nI've come here for an honest discussion.
I am not evil—and despite being\na murderer, neither is Alex.
We merely hunt heretics in accordance\nwith the will of the goddess.
We carry out justice! Our deeds are pure—\nand Ilias's love for them is without bounds!
Are you going somewhere with this?
Return to me, my dear Alex!\nHunt heretics at my side once more!
That is the only way for someone with\nyour bloody hands to live an honest life.
Without the just cause the goddess's name\nprovides for your deeds, you're merely a\ncommon killer—nay, a beast!
Say, Alex? I know I said I was just gonna\nopen the way, but I take it back.
I'm just gonna introduce this guy's face\nto my fist for a sec if ya don't mind.
Aaaah ha ha! Very good, Alex!
A beast has no need for independent\nthought. A beast just needs to do as\nit is told—it needs to kill!
THAT is how you will find happiness.\nNow return to me!
The children you're trying to raise into a\nnew generation of assassins are orphans.
Did you choose them because you thought\nsuch people more likely to obey you?
Just like when I feared I would be\ndriven out of the Church?
Well, I'm not like that anymore.
I have a home. I BELONG.
*sigh* It seems this conversation\nis going nowhere fast.
The day is yours, my loyal warriors.\nLeave none alive!
He's gonna take off! What a jerk!
Don't let him get away, Alex!
They'll never follow me this far.
Hmph! That foolish woman made\na grave error by refusing my offer.
She must truly be regretting it now...\nif corpses can feel regret! Aaah ha ha!
You're not killing me—OR my friends.
How ironic that the skills you taught me\nshould prove useful in tracking you down.
Curses! Why didn't I bring at least one\nof my assassins as a bodyguard?!
It's time to answer for your crimes.
S-stay away... Stay away from me!
And you were so confident earlier!
Perhaps you finally understand how it\nfeels to be the hunted rather than\nthe hunter.
You're here to kill me...\nYou're here to KILL me!

Of course you are, you murderer!
No matter how you try to pretend
otherwise, you're nothing but a
bloodthirsty beast at your core!
I wouldn't be so sure of that. Haaaah!
I'm glad to see you all safe.
Looks like you found the priest.
He ain't movin'. Like, at all.\nDidja actually...?
He's just unconscious.\nI was going to knock him out with the flat\nof my blade, but he fainted before I could.
Check out how scared he looks!\nWhat a chump! Bwaaa ha ha ha!
I'm guessing this experience will be\nenough to deter his evil ways.
Could I have a moment, everyone?
What happened today made me\nrealize something.
When I decided to help orphans,\nI thought of two ways to do so.
The first was to help someone who\nwas already undertaking that task.\nAnd the second was to do it myself.
I decided there was only so much a\nwoman like me could do, and quickly\nabandoned the second option.
But now I've changed my mind.
I think you know the answer to that.
I'm so very glad to have met you all...
